steps.text: Making Dough - total resting: 2 hours, 15 minutes

In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a dough hook attachment , dissolve the yeast in the warm water. Sift together the flour and cornstarch, and add it to the yeast mixture along with the sugar and oil.
Turn on the mixer to the lowest setting and let it go until a smooth dough ball is formed. Cover with a damp cloth and let it rest for 2 hours.

After your dough has rested for 2 hours, add the baking powder to the dough and turn the mixer on to the lowest setting. At this point, if the dough looks dry or you're having trouble incorporating the baking powder, add 1-2 teaspoons water. Gently knead the dough until it becomes smooth again.
Cover with a damp cloth and let it rest for another 15 minutes.
Making filling
Heat the oil in a wok over medium high heat. Add the onion and stir-fry for a minute.
Turn heat down to medium-low, and add the sugar, soy sauce, oyster sauce, sesame oil, and dark soy. Stir and cook until the mixture starts to bubble up.
Add the chicken stock and flour, cooking for a couple minutes until thickened. Remove from the heat and stir in the roast pork (see Charsiu pork recipe).
Set aside filling to cool. If you make the filling ahead of time, cover and refrigerate to prevent it from drying out.
Assembly/ steaming
Cut parchment paper into 12 4x4 inch squares.

Roll the fully rested dough into a long tube and divide it into 12 equal pieces. Press each piece of dough into a disc about 4 1/2 inches in diameter (it should be thicker in the center and thinner around the edges).
Add some filling and pleat the buns until they're closed on top.
Place each bun on a parchment paper square, and place in a steaming basket.

Instant pot method: fill instant pot with 1 cup of water and place trivet down in the pot. Place steamer basket on the trivet and close the bamboo lid on top. Close InstantPot lid, put valve on sealing, and pressure cook on high for 4 minutes with 10 minutes natural release.

notes:
- Bao buns must be all steamed before storing/ freezing - to freeze, ensure the buns are fully cooled, place them on parchment piece and then freeze in single layer in freezer before putting them in a bag 
- to reheat, can use the instant pot method or cover with a damp paper cloth and microwave for 40 seconds

Turn off the mixer. Pour in HALF the dry ingredients, drape a kitchen towel over the stand mixer to protect yourself and your kitchen from flying flour and pulse the mixer at low speed about 5 times, a second or two each time. Repeat with rest of the dry ingredients.

Take a peek — if there is still a lot of flour on the surface of the dough, pulse a couple of times more; if not, remove the towel. steps.text: Ragu Sauce
Prep beef by cutting off fatty parts and sectioning into chunks (large-medium size) Pat beef dry and sprinkle with salt and pepper
Sear Beef: Heat 1 tbsp olive oil over high heat in a heavy based pot. Add beef and sear each piece aggressively on all sides until very browned (3  minutes in total), then remove onto a plate.
Turn stove down to medium low and add remaining 0.5 tbsp of olive oil.
Soffrito: Add garlic and onion and sauté for 2 minutes. Then add the carrots and celery and sauté slowly for 5 minutes.

Add remaining Ragu ingredients (spices, wine, tomatoes, tomato paste and water) and return the beef to the pot (including pooled juices). Turn the stove up and bring it to a simmer, then turn it down to low so it's bubbling very very gently.
Slow cook: Cover the pot and let it cook for 2 hours or until beef is tender enough to shred. Occasionally stir and add more water to the sauce if the sauce is sticking to the bottom of the pot.
Shred: Remove beef then coarsely shred with 2 forks. Return beef to the pot. Simmer for 30 minutes until sauce is reduced and thickened - beef will soften slightly more during this step.
Final season: Do a taste test and adjust the seasoning to your taste with 1 tsp of fish sauce. ALSO, add about 1 tsp of sugar to taste.

ingredients.fdcQuery: Chickpeas (garbanzo beans, bengal gram), mature seeds, canned, drained solids
Vitasoy USA Azumaya, Extra Firm Tofu
Tomatoes, red, ripe, raw, year round average

steps.text: Drain chickpeas,  cube tofu into bite sized pieces and dice tomato into wedges.
To a large wok, add 2 teaspoons of oil and then add garlic and ginger and stir-fry until fragrant.
To the wok, add drained chickpeas along with all the spices (except fenugreek and sugar) and cook on medium-high until spices are toasted and the chickpeas are a little browned.
Add in the butter chicken sauce, cubed tofu and tomatoes - increase heat until boil is reached and then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer the curry for about 10 minutes
After 10 minutes, open lid and with a spatula, smash some of the chickpeas to thicken the curry and break apart the tomato wedges as well.
Add sugar and fenugreek. Season with salt as necessary
Serve with basmati rice
Mix all sauce ingredients (except the salt) and set aside (do not add water yet - you'll use the water to wash out the sauce bowl)
Cut all veggies into thin strips (zucchini into thin half moons)
Defrost shrimp and cup tofu into thin strips (first press with some paper towels to get rid of excess moisture.

To a very large wok , add half of the oil and then stir fry all the veggies (except for the garlic) at high heat with some water and the mushroom powder until just softened (But still crisp). The order to add was: zucchini, carrots and then peppers and onions together. Remove veggies from heat and set aside.
To the same wok, add the tofu strips in along with about 2 Tbsp of sauce. Let it sear on one side before flipping.
Add shrimp to the tofu along with 1 Tbsp of sauce and cook on high heat until shrimp is fully cooked. Remove the protein and set aside.
Boil noodles for about 3-5 minutes until softened.

To the same wok, add the remainder of the oil and all the minced garlic and stir fry until softened. Add all the noodles along with all of the sauce and 1/3 cup of water. Stir fry on medium-high heat until the sauce is fully absorbed into the noodles.
Add everything (veggies and protein) into the wok along with 2 tbsp of sesame oil and 0.5 tsp of salt and stir to incorporate everything.
Taste and add more salt if necessary.
